data.name: useSkinWeatherIcons.ToolTip
data.value: This option will replace the default MediaPortal 128x128 weather icons with those used with basichome. These will then be used in place of the standard icons with the weather section. A backup is made and can be restored by selecting this link again.

data.name: disableBGSharing.ToolTip
data.value: By default Background that match on image folder, random and time per image are comboned into a single control. An example is TV and TvSeries, the default action is to share this image between menu items if they share the properties above. If you want the background displayed to be differnet when switching between matching Menu Items then select this option.

data.name: gbScreenRes.ToolTip
data.value:
Scaling configuration
Select the resoloution that most closes matches that of the display you will be using for MediaPortal.
There are two sizes FullHD (1920x1080) and Std HD (1280x720). If the menu editor is run on the display you will be using to run MediaPortal on you can accept the Auto Detected value.
If you use RDP to configure your system or are generting a BasicHome for a differnet system you may want to overide the deteted setting.

data.name: pictureBox3.ToolTip
data.value:
This tab list the current images set as default, these will be used if the multiimage option is disabled.
Menu items can share backdrops, if the description has a + at the end the tooltip will display the additional menu items that share this background.

data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
The alternative SplashScreen option pack is not installed please click the link below to install these files.
SplashScreen's are only be displayed if MediaPortal is configured to start in fullscreen mode and the
'Use alternative fullsceen Splashscreen'
option is enabled in Mediaportal configuration.

data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
StreamedMPEditor is a stand alone editor for the StreamedMP Skin.
Alows for generation of both Vertical and Horizontal Basichome menus. and control of RSS and weather display using the InfoService plugin.
